1 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Appropriation. (1) There is appropriated $100,000 from the Montana-
2 Ireland trade and development special revenue account to the department of commerce for the biennium
3 beginning July 1, 2025, for implementing the provisions of Senate Bill No. 320.
4 (2) It is the intent of the legislature that the appropriation be included in the base budget for the
5 department of commerce for the biennium beginning July 1, 2027.
6
7 COORDINATION SECTION. Section 3. Coordination instruction. If both House Bill No. 483 and
8 [this act] and an act that provides property tax relief are passed and approved, and if the actual revenues from
9 the 95 school equalization mills for fiscal year 2026 or fiscal year 2027, as certified by the department of
10 revenue, are below the fiscal year 2025 revenue estimate in House Joint Resolution No. 2 of $441.624 million,
11 then the amount used to evaluate the projected increase or decrease in revenue from the 95 school
12 equalization mills under [section 5 of House Bill No. 483], amending 20-9-336, must be determined by
13 comparing the actual revenues to the 2025 revenue estimate in House Joint Resolution No. 2 of $441.624
14 million.
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
17 - END -
